00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:31.000
The control console is designed around a standard PC platform.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:37.000
The PT6 console is separated from the radio frequency generator console.

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:46.000
The main machine interface is straightforward.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:50.000
Part geometrical data is entered into the system via windows like environment.

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:55.000
Compensation for spring in and spring out can 
 be added separately to each arched section.

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
The program includes machine diagnostics and on-line help features.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
Parts can be graphically represented on the computer screen.

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.000
The PT6 can also form aluminum extrusions.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:28.000
The extrusions must first be encapsulated in UHMW form 
 to support the piece during the forming operation.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:36.000
The UHMW form supports the sections of the profile that 
 are subjected to compressive forces during the forming process.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
There is no curing or cooling cycle when forming aluminum extrusions

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:44.000
The part is merely loaded into the machine and the bending cycle initiated.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:50.000
The machine will automatically then form the component.

